    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-02T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-02T07:00:00-05:00" n="216"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1030</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BTH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Birch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-02T12:00:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1914, 12 noon</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2:80 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>It is affirmed, though unofficially, that Portugal, in accordance with English
                    treaty obligation, will enter the war. It is my opinion that the above action
                    will unquestionably be taken as soon as preparations shall have been
                    completed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BTH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Birch</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
